<br>
  It wasn't so clear in others posts here, so I'll clear this up.<br>
Here you are misinterpreting fault tolerance, Raid 0-5(something you do in case one hard drive crashes you have a complete back up on another) for a trick to speed up your pc.  It will slow you down, not make it quicker.<br>
  Its a good idea but we only use this on our server, which in turn gets alot of back ups from our normal PC's.<br>
In your case I think it would be an unnecessary expense, just put your back ups on your second partition and then if you trash windows, you can reload it on C and still have all your info on D.<br>
  There is no way I know of to make your HD's faster, besides, SCSI, and maybe using Fat32 over NTFS for gaming.<br>
